110 words 
</P>
</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
PAPERBACKS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 AN UNCOMMON SCOLD compiled by Abby Adams (Fireside: $8; 268 pp., illustrated). 
Adams' collection of quotes from famous women ranges in subject from modern 
relationships ("As I look around the West End these days, it seems to me that 
outside every thin girl is a fat man, trying to get in" -- Katherine Whitehorn) 
to the value of learning ("Lack of education is an extraordinary handicap when 
one is being offensive" -- Josephine Tey). These bons and mals mots could spice 
up a letter or a term paper -- or just provide a distraction while waiting for 
a guest or a phone call: As Marilyn Monroe remarked, "I've been on a calendar, 
but never on time." 
</P>
