<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 NOUVELLE SOUL by Barbara Summers (Amistad Press: $8.95; 247 pp.). Summers' 
stories are set in middle-class neighborhoods in New York, the Eastern Seaboard 
and Paris; her characters' relationships are complicated by questions of social 
mobility and deeply ingrained racial attitudes.Some of the most affecting 
stories are told from multiple viewpoints, including "Free Skies," an account 
of the first Afro-American woman stunt pilot. A blend of strength and humor 
gives these stories a rare appeal. As three daughters clear out years of their 
mother's accumulated junk in "Nothing Like Daddy," one reflects, "Black women 
always last to give up. We just don't know how. Mother to the world even if 
we're a single mother. If we collapse, the world collapses. Women running the 
world and got to carry it too." 
</P>
