<TEXT>
<P>
 THE GUINESS BOOK OF RECORDS edited by Peter Matthews (Bantam: $6.99; 819 pp., 
illustrated, paperback original). The 1994 edition of the famous reference book 
contains a great deal of useful information about the fastest, tallest, 
biggest, etc. Unfortunately, the serious aspects of the volume have been 
overshadowed by its sillier contents: The world's largest cookie (34 feet in 
diameter) contained almost 4 million chocolate chips; the largest cocktail 
included 1,650 gallons of rum, triple sec, sour mix, orange juice and 
grenadine. Even more depressing are the lists of dim-bulb stunts people stage 
to get into the book -- jumping on pogo sticks, threading needles, balancing 
milk crates, etc. 
