RERUNS TO REWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN KING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 TNT presents an edited version of the award-winning miniseries Shogun (Sunday, 
beginning at 7 a.m.), based on James Michener's book about feudal Japan. 
Richard Chamberlain and Toshiro Mifune stars. 
</P>
<P>
 The late great Don Ameche guests on Columbo (Monday at 11 a.m. on A&E) in a 
thriller about an art critic who murders his wealthy uncle to get at his art 
collection. 
</P>
<P>
 Clown Leslie Nielsen of the "Naked Gun" movies shows his dramatic side on a 
vintage Columbo (Monday at 12:30 p.m. on A&E). 
</P>
<P>
 Nick at Nite repeats the very first episode of The Dick Van Dyke Show (Monday 
at 11 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Ontkean ("Twin Peaks") plays a new boy at school in The Partridge 
Family (Tuesday at 8 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
<P>
 Lucy tells Ricky she's pregnant in the classic "Lucy Is Enciente " episode of 
I Love Lucy (Tuesday at 9 p.m. on Nickelodeon). 
</P>
