<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; HEALTH: HONORING COUNTY SUPERVISOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The AIDS Healthcare Foundation Clinic will honor Los Angeles County Supervisor 
Ed Edelman at a ribbon-cutting ceremony next Thursday for his years of service 
to people with AIDS and HIV, the virus that causes the disease. 
</P>
<P>
 Edelman will retire from his term on the County Board of Supervisors at the 
end of the year. During his tenure, he helped establish a ward at County-USC 
Medical Center for people with HIV. He was instrumental in founding the Chris 
Brownlie Hospice in Elysian Park. 
</P>
<P>
 The ceremony begins at 10 a.m. at the clinic, which is housed at Cedars-Sinai 
Medical Towers, 8635 W. 3rd St., Los Angeles. 
</P>
