<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; CALIFORNIA CORNER; FESTIVALS, FEASTS & FAIRS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 VENTURA -- Get out the hats and thongs for the California Beach Party, 10 
a.m.-5 p.m. April 23-24 along the beachside promenade from the Ventura County 
Fairgrounds to the pier. $5.50, general; $3.50, seniors; free for kids 12 and 
under. (805) 444-JACK. 
</P>
<P>
 PETALUMA -- The Butter and Egg Days Parade is at noon Saturday on Petaluma 
Boulevard, and festivities continue all day in Putnam Plaza. Free. Stay in town 
for the Semiannual Antique Faire, 8 a.m.-4 p.m. next Sunday along Kentucky 
Street. More than 175 vendors expected. Free. (707) 769-0429. 
</P>
<P>
 SAN DIEGO -- Secondhand treasures await at the Berkeley Rummage sale, a 
floating event on the upper deck of Berkeley, an 1898 ferryboat. 9 a.m.-4 p.m. 
Saturday and next Sunday. The Berkeley is at the Embarcadero, 1306 N. Harbor 
Drive. (619) 234-9153. 
</P>
<P>
 ARVIN -- Poppies, lupine and other seasonal blooms are celebrated at the Arvin 
Wildflower Festival, Saturday and next Sunday at DiGiorgio Park, Hill Street 
and Haven Drive. A parade is at 10 a.m. Saturday (starting at Bear Mountain 
Boulevard and Campus Drive), followed by the festival, 11 a.m.-6 p.m. Saturday; 
noon-6 p.m. Sunday. (805) 854-2265. 
</P>
<P>
 LAGUNA BEACH -- The Laguna Beach Classic 10K/5K/1K Race is next Sunday, 
starting at the Sawdust Festival grounds, 935 Laguna Canyon Road. $20, 5K and 
10K registration; $15, 1K. The 5K race starts at 7:45 a.m.; the 10K at 8:20, 
and the 1K at 9:15. (Race-day registration starts at 6:30 a.m.) (714) 494-3980. 
</P>
<P>
 Call listed phone numbers for directions. MARY FRANCES SMITH 
</P>
