<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWS, TIPS & BARGAINS; VAT -- A TAXING ISSUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 VAT -- Value Added Tax -- is a sales tax with a difference: It's usually 
refundable to foreigners. To get refunds, travelers must make a minimum 
purchase per merchant and must have refund forms stamped by customs officials 
before leaving the country.Below are minimum expenditures required to obtain a 
refund, and the amount of the purchase price that is VAT. Must stores include 
the VAT in their price tags, instead of showing the tax separately, so it's 
easy to overlook how much money is going to taxes. For a free brochure, write 
or fax Europe Tax-free Shopping at its American headquarters, 111 W. Monroe 
St., Suite 2100E, Chicago, Ill. 60603; fax (312) 346-6211. 
</P>
<P>
 All prices in U.S. Dollars 03,13,10,12 Country Minimum VAT levels Austria $85 
16.7% Belgium $200 17% Britain $75 14.9% Denmark $90 20% Finland $17 18% France 
$350 15.7% Germany $30 13% Greece $165 11.5-15.3% Hungary $300 20% Italy 
$180+VAT 11.5-16% Luxembourg $85 13% Netherlands $160 14.9% Norway $40 18% 
Portugal $60+VAT 13.8-23% Slovenia $65 9.1-24.2% Spain $110 13% Sweden $12 20% 
Source: Europe Tax-free Shopping  
</P>
</TEXT>
