<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORE ON VISAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your charts on obtaining visas (News, Tips and Bargains, March 20 and 27 and 
April 3) were noted with interest since the San Francisco company credited with 
the information didn't bother to point out that consulates in Los Angeles may 
have slightly different rules or prices. This often happens among consulates 
for the same country in different cities. There is also frequently a legal 
jurisdictional situation that makes it necessary to secure visas in Los Angeles 
if you are a resident of Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
 ROBERT L. STRICKLIN, President, Visas International, Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
