<HEADLINE>
<P>
GOLD COUNTRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Odd that writer Eric Malnic didn't mention the historic Fallon Theatre in his 
article on Gold Rush towns ("Mining Gold Country," March 27). 
</P>
<P>
 When the state bought Columbia, it reinforced the aged brick walls and tower 
of the theater, made other refurbishments and leased it to College of the 
Pacific (now University of the Pacific) for summer theater activity. COP 
students got an opportunity to act in three plays in six weeks, providing a 
stock experience not available anywhere in Northern California. 
</P>
<P>
 WILLIAM R. FITTS, West Hollywood 
</P>
</TEXT>
