<HEADLINE>
<P>
RESTAURANT RAVE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 You missed the greatest restaurant in the Tucson area, bar none ("No Glitz 
Grub," April 3).La Roque, in Nogales, Mexico, beats all in Tucson. (I've eaten 
in all!) It's about 60 miles south of Tucson. 
</P>
<P>
 Big, big menu. A few Mexican dishes. Last time, two weeks ago, I had Gulf 
shrimp in light garlic. Others at my table had marvelous steak. Choices were 
about $10 each. Outstanding margaritas. 
</P>
<P>
 Park on U.S. side, 50 yards from border, for $4. Walk through border house, 
turn left, walk about 150 yards to restaurant at foot of cliff. 
</P>
<P>
 JOHN C. HABECKER, Cucamonga 
</P>
