<HEADLINE>
<P>
LANGUAGE LAPSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 This is both a thank you (the section is wonderful, I love it) and a 
correction. The letter from Anatol Charey on the bazaars in Istanbul (March 27) 
refers to a merchant's son who speaks many languages. The first language 
mentioned is not Latino, but Ladino (an archaic blend of Hebrew and Spanish). 
</P>
<P>
 SHIRA PASKINS, Long Beach 
</P>
