<P>
 ** Phish, "Hoist," Elektra. As the underappreciated '60s band Spirit once did, 
this Vermont quartet incorporates a Hebrew prayer into the rock of its third 
major-label album.And like Spirit, Phish offers an idiosyncratic blend of chops 
and cleverness. Unlike Spirit, there's little depth of imagination or emotion 
to make it more than a set of quirky (and not very memorable) musical and 
lyrical twists. 
</P>
