<HEADLINE>
<P>
WOMEN FIREFIGHTERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * Hayden D. Hamilton's letter (April 10), in reference to the "wall" test for 
police candidates, also included a tongue-in-cheek comment about women 
firefighters.  
</P>
<P>
 As a battalion chief of the Los Angeles City Fire Department, and a supporter 
of the women firefighters, I take issue with his remarks.His comment, "We now 
have female firefighters who can't push a ladder up to a burning building," 
does not apply to the women of the L.A. City Fire Department. Those women all 
passed one of the severest tests of strength and willpower when they passed 
through the drill tower. They then were evaluated for 12 months by officers in 
the fire stations. 
</P>
<P>
 Women firefighters have worked diligently and with courage to gain the 
respected position of firefighter, and should not be castigated by lighthearted 
comments.  
</P>
<P>
 JOHN J. ADAMS, Battalion Chief 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles City Fire Department 
</P>
</TEXT>
