<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: MAN DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY CAR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Simi Valley man died from multiple injuries after being struck by a 
suspected drunk driver about 10:30 p.m. Friday evening on Whitcomb Avenue in 
Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Raphael Lachmiller, 54, was struck and killed while walking from his car to 
his family's house, said Sgt. Ron Lompart of the Simi Valley Police Department. 
</P>
<P>
 Michael Rodriguez, 39, of Simi Valley was stopped several blocks from the 
scene and arrested on suspicion of vehicular manslaughter, felony hit-and-run, 
drunk driving and evading arrest. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said Rodriguez collided with a parked car on Brandon Avenue without 
stopping. A witness followed the car and saw the suspect hit another parked 
car, before rounding the corner onto Whitcomb Avenue and hitting Lachmiller.  
</P>
<P>
 The suspect continued without stopping, hitting another vehicle before jumping 
from his car and trying to flee from police, Lompart said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rodriguez is being held in lieu of $50,000 bail at the Ventura County Jail. 
SCOTT HADLY 
</P>
</TEXT>
