<HEADLINE>
<P>
LEGISLATURE TO BLAME FOR BUSINESS EXODUS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * I hope your two Sunday commentaries "A Difficult Decision for a Booster of 
Los Angeles" and "Blaming the Victims" (April 3), wakes up the voting public, 
or at the very least, our incompetent and inept politicians in Sacramento. 
</P>
<P>
 I have spent many years both in law enforcement and business.I can assure you, 
the rapid departure of the tax-paying base to other states is the direct result 
of the state Legislature's wooing the citizen looking for a "free ride" and the 
votes of the criminal's families. Not to mention lining the pockets with a 
multitude of perks and pensions for each elected position. (I only get one 
pension.) 
</P>
<P>
 Profit is not a dirty word. Businesses create tax-paying jobs and are able to 
expand with profit. Stop punishing achievement. 
</P>
<P>
 My small business netted $5,000 last year, but my state tax alone was $6,700. 
This state has become a joke. Vote the bums out. 
</P>
<P>
 ART TUBER 
</P>
<P>
 Woodland Hills 
</P>
