<HEADLINE>
<P>
BAGPIPES DRIVING YOU NUTS? -- HE'S GOT A MUM IDEA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Reuters 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A British technology teacher said Friday he has invented a gadget that could 
stop bagpipe-players from driving their neighbors mad. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Watchman-Atkinson of Gateshead in northeastern England said he got the 
idea while attending a Scottish wedding. Bagpipes have a distinctive sound that 
some people find annoying. 
</P>
<P>
 To use Atkinson's device, the player does not blow pipes but rather fingers a 
chanter -- the pipe on which the melody is played -- and the notes are 
recorded. They can then be played back later using headphones. 
</P>
<P>
 "The machine reacts as bagpipes would but only the person playing can hear it. 
It is better than driving everyone else mad -- very useful for practicing," 
Atkinson said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
