<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE ELLING 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hawaii, fielding a team of gap hitters, found all the alleys Saturday night 
and rolled to a 13-7 victory over Cal State Northridge in a Western Athletic 
Conference game before 2,956 at Rainbow Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 Hawaii (23-20, 5-9 in conference play) jumped to a 2-0 lead in the second 
against Aaron D'Aoust on doubles by Jason Ross and Sy Farinas. 
</P>
<P>
 In the third, Corey Ishigo's double to right-center drove in two runs as 
Hawaii scored four times for a 6-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge had beaten Hawaii seven consecutive times entering the game, but 
managed only one hit through three innings.STEVE ELLING 
