<TEXT>
<P>
 Shannon Jones hit two home runs and drove in five runs to lift the Cal State 
Northridge softball team to 4-3 and 10-0 victories in a Western Athletic 
Conference doubleheader Saturday at Northridge. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior third baseman had a grand slam and two doubles in the second game. 
Jones has hit five home runs in her last 10 at-bats. 
</P>
<P>
 Northridge (35-6, 10-2 in conference play) built a 4-0 third-inning lead and 
held off a late San Diego State rally in the first game. In the second game, 
Terri Pearson was three for three for the Matadors, who pounded out 11 hits 
against the Aztecs (18-18-1, 1-8-1). COLLEGE BASEBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Mission 9-13, East L.A. 7-14 -- Dave Valdez belted a two-run home run in the 
sixth, giving Mission (21-14, 12-7) the lead for good in the first game of a 
Southern California Athletic Conference doubleheader.  
</P>
<P>
 Valdez finished the day six for nine with seven runs and four RBIs.  
</P>
<P>
 Gary Mathews of Mission was four for seven with six RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Oxnard 10, Santa Barbara 3 -- Jess Olivares had four hits and three RBIs for 
Oxnard in a Western State Conference game at Cabrillo Park. Ray Franco had two 
hits and three RBIs and Ryan Glass added an RBI double. 
