<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; OLSEN HELPS TITANS ROUT UNLV, 20-1 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Behind D.C. Olsen and Tony Miranda, Cal State Fullerton pounded Nevada Las 
Vegas, 20-1, in a Big West Conference baseball game Saturday at Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Olsen went three for five with two homers (one grand slam), a double and seven 
runs batted in for Fullerton (30-8, 8-3). 
</P>
<P>
 Miranda hit a leadoff homer, his second, in the sixth and finished three for 
five with three RBIs. 
</P>
<P>
 Titan pitcher Matt Wagner improved to 9-0, pitching seven innings, allowing 
only three hits and striking out 10. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference baseball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 6-4, Westmont 3-3 -- Jason Brissey hit a home run 
in the bottom of the ninth inning of the second game to lead Southern 
California College to the upset sweep of first-place Westmont (20-13, 8-5). 
</P>
<P>
 The Vanguards are 15-22, 5-8. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Cal State Fullerton 1-1, Hawaii 0-0 -- Fullerton manufactured runs in the 
bottom of the final inning of each game to upset eighth-ranked Hawaii in both 
ends of a doubleheader at Hawaii. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton, the home team because the entire season series was played this week 
in Hawaii to save travel costs, improved to 20-25, 9-9 in the Big West. Hawaii 
is 40-9 and 16-4. 
</P>
<P>
 Jennifer Mortensen (13-14) won both games, the second with five innings of 
relief. She also scored the winning run in the second game, singling to open 
the sixth, going to second on a groundout, third on a single and scoring on a 
wild pitch. 
</P>
<P>
 Fullerton scored the only run in the eight-inning first game without the 
benefit of a hit. Laurie LoForti reached base on an error, advanced to second 
on a wild pitch, to third on a fielder's choice and scored on another wild 
pitch. Mortensen pitched a three-hitter, striking out five and walking one. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference softball: 
</P>
<P>
 Southern California College 5-4, Azusa Pacific 4-0 -- Amy Lewis had two hits 
and three RBIs in the two games for SCC, and she drove in the winning run in 
the first game. Carrie Nelson added three hits and three runs scored for SCC 
(36-7, 12-2). 
