<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANTA MARGARITA GIRLS, SADDLEBACK BOYS WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Santa Margarita girls' team won three events and the Saddleback boys two 
as they won team titles at the Tustin Relays Saturday at Rancho Santiago 
College. 
</P>
<P>
 Orange County boys' teams took eight of the top 10 places and girls' teams 
seven of the top 10 as the meet drew a field of 54, the largest in the 36-year 
history of the event. 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Margarita's girls' relays won the 3,200 (9:49), 6,400 (22:06.8) and 
triple jump (101 feet 3 inches for three jumpers) and scored 71 points. Long 
Beach Wilson scored 51. 
</P>
<P>
 Saddleback's boys won the shuttle hurdles in 59.3 and the 3,200 relay in 
8:16.13 and scored 54 points; Wilson had 41. Saddleback also lost two races by 
one-tenth of a second: the 400 to Irvine (43.8-43.9) and the 1,600 to Wilson 
(3:27.3-3:27.4). 
</P>
<P>
 Top individual performances included Reggie Curry of Tustin, who leaped 46-10 
1/2 in the triple jump. 
</P>
</TEXT>
