</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 27-year-old man was arrested on suspicion of burglary Saturday after police 
said he smashed through a glass door of Blockbuster Video and grabbed some 
video equipment. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said Luther Adam Bell of Garden Grove also was being held on 
parole violations that could make him a "third-strike" candidate for more 
prison time if convicted. California law now mandates lengthy prison terms for 
people convicted of three felonies. 
</P>
<P>
 An Anaheim police task force had been watching the store at 10524 Valley View 
Street because of a series of Blockbuster break-ins. 
