 Sheriff's Lt. Jay Mendez said investigators are trying to determine whether 
the overdoses were a murder-suicide attempt. 
</P>
<P>
 He said the son of the elderly woman visited their westside condominium near 
Katella Avenue and Knott Street shortly before 5 p.m. and discovered the 
unconscious family members. Mendez said the younger woman suffered from 
cerebral palsy. 
