<P>
WOMAN DISABLES CAR, THWARTING CARJACKER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALICIA DI RADO, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 69-year-old woman confronted by a carjacker quickly disabled the ignition 
before abandoning the car to him, police said Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 A teen-ager, armed with a handgun, approached the woman about 9 p.m. Friday in 
the parking lot of the Park West Apartments complex on the 3800 block of 
Parkview Lane and demanded her Chrysler New Yorker, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The woman, whose name was not released, turned on a device that prevented the 
car's ignition from working, Irvine Police Sgt. Jeff Kermode said. She ran from 
the car as the would-be carjacker tried to start it. 
</P>
<P>
 When it wouldn't, he ran, too. 
</P>
<P>
 Evidence obtained at the scene led them to a 16-year-old who lives in Santa 
Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 The youth, whose name was not released because he is a juvenile, was booked at 
Orange County Juvenile Hall on suspicion of carjacking, police said. 
</P>
