<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; IRAQ; AIR COVER RESUMES IN 'NO FLY' ZONE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 U.S. and allied jet fighters resumed patrols over northern Iraq after a 
one-day halt in the wake of Thursday's downing of two American helicopters by 
U.S. warplanes, the Pentagon said. The U.S. European Command ordered the 
protective flights resumed on a reduced schedule over a "no fly" zone north of 
the 36th Parallel. The zone was imposed after the 1991 Persian Gulf War by the 
allies to protect Kurds in northern Iraq. 
