<HEADLINE>
<P>
WORLD IN BRIEF; SOUTH AFRICA; TEACHER CHARGED IN SERIAL KILLING CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Police in Cape Town have charged a schoolteacher as South Africa's worst 
serial killer, dubbed "the Station Strangler," after 21 boys were slain in an 
eight-year rampage. The strangler stalked his victims, boys ages 9 to 15, at 
railway stations, lured them away and dumped their bodies in scrubland. Police 
said the suspect, charged with one murder, is an elementary school teacher with 
a history of mental illness. 
</P>
