<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRING ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roosevelt 9, Locke 2 -- Shortstop Juan Carlos Rodriguez went one-for-three 
with three RBIs as the Roughriders easily won a Southeastern Conference game 
Tuesday at Locke. TRACK 
</P>
<P>
 If the competition were wondering about Michael Granville's strategy for the 
800 meters in the Arcadia/Foot Locker Invitational, they weren't alone.The Bell 
Gardens High sophomore wasn't quite sure either. 
</P>
<P>
 "Sometimes I have different feelings for strategies, but I didn't decide until 
I was right on the starting line," Granville said. 
</P>
<P>
 His choice at the April 9 meet was a wise one. 
</P>
<P>
 Granville, who was named the Indoor Athlete of the Year by Track & Field News 
magazine, led from the start and held off a late charge from Milton Campbell of 
Atlanta Douglass to win in 1 minute 51.90 seconds -- the fastest high school 
time in the nation this season. 
</P>
<P>
 In the distance medley relay, Loyola's Hugo Rodriguez, Vince Cogan, Brian Duff 
and Jason Barreda ran to victory in 10:16.15, the fastest in the nation this 
season. KIRBY LEE 
</P>
</TEXT>
