<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRING ROUNDUP; RODRIGUEZ LEADS ROOSEVELT HIT PARADE OVER GARFIELD, 14-0 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHARLES SMITH 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Juan Carlos Rodriguez should have traded in his batting helmet for a drum 
major's hat. 
</P>
<P>
 The senior shortstop led a Roosevelt hit parade, going four-for-five with two 
RBIs in a 14-0 victory over Garfield in a Southeastern Conference game at 
Roosevelt. 
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt, which pounded out 16 hits, scored nine of its 14 runs in the first 
three innings. CHARLES SMITH 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story 
</P>
</TYPE>
