<HEADLINE>
<P>
SPRING ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Garfield 3, Jordan 0 -- Garfield beat host Jordan, 15-8, 15-4, 15-6, in a 
Central League match Wednesday led by spikers Cisko Sianez and Arturo Sanchez, 
and setter Luis Munoz's 32 assists. 
</P>
<P>
 Eagle Rock 3, Belmont 0 -- Luis Alvarado and Ben Collado each had five kills 
in a losing effort for Belmont.Eagle Rock won 17-15, 15-12, 15-5. BOYS' 
SWIMMING 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate 104, Garfield 75 -- Bruce Monroy won the 200 individual medley and 
the 100 butterfly to lead the Rams boys in a dual East-North League meet 
Monday. Bulldog Johnny Vallejo remains undefeated in diving. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Park 99, Bell 74 -- Eagles Luis Torres won the 200 freestyle and 
500 freestyle in Bell's loss to the Spartans on Monday. SOFTBALL 
</P>
<P>
 Fremont 13 Locke 9 -- Pathfinder Shatana Smith struck out 12 and had four 
hits, including a home run, in a Southeastern Conference victory Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Garfield 7, Bell 3 -- Bulldog Alma Limon gave up all three Eagle runs in the 
first inning in an Eastern League victory Wednesday. Limon's third-inning hit 
down the middle scored two runs. 
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt 18, Huntington Park 0 -- Liz Ballesteros threw a one-hitter and 
Jennifer Brambilia had a triple and drove in five runs in a Central League 
blowout Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate 9, Jordan 3 -- Ivonne Arrizaga gave up one earned run and had nine 
strikeouts in an Eastern League triumph Wednesday. 
