COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHWEST: CRENSHAW; MINORITY-OWNED FIRMS TO GET AID 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bank of America and the U.S. Department of Commerce have announced a joint 
effort to help increase the number of minority-owned businesses in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 At the Bank of America branch at 4103 S. Western Ave., bank and federal 
officials detailed plans of the venture last week. The federal Minority 
Enterprise Growth Assistance Center in Los Angeles will help minority business 
owners prepare loan applications. 
</P>
<P>
 The center will also offer management and technical assistance and establish a 
panel to review rejected loan applications. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (213) 895-0224. 
</P>
