<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: HIGHLAND PARK; 3 KILLED AS TRUCK CRASHES INTO WALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three Highland Park men were killed last week when their speeding truck failed 
to negotiate a curve on Figueroa Street at York Boulevard, hit a fire hydrant 
and ran into the wall of Donna's Hamburgers, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
 Police Detective Richard Lopez of the Central Traffic Division said all three 
men were killed instantly Tuesday night: Victor Grijalva, who was the 
25-year-old driver, and his passengers, Mario Gonzales, 28, and Andy Fierro, 
26. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that the truck clipped a car as it headed south on 
Figueroa shortly before midnight and appeared to be going 95 to 100 m.p.h. 
Police investigators estimated that the Toyota 4-Runner truck hit the wall 
going 85 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 Police suspect narcotics were involved and are awaiting toxicology reports 
from the coroner's office.  
</P>
<P>
 Lopez said it appeared that none of the men were wearing seat belts. 
</P>
<P>
 "It couldn't make the curve and went straight and ran off the roadway," Lopez 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've had other accidents there," he said, adding that engineers are looking 
into widening the curve to make it less sharp. MARY ANNE PEREZ 
</P>
</TEXT>
