<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: EAST: EAST LOS ANGELES; MEETING PLANNED ON BUS FARE INCREASES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Metropolitan Transportation Authority has scheduled a meeting Monday for 
Eastside residents to provide information on proposed bus rate increases and 
service reductions. 
</P>
<P>
 The 6 p.m. meeting at Resurrection Church, 3324 Opal St., will provide 
information regarding a public hearing scheduled for 10 a.m. Saturday at the 
Board of Supervisors hearing room, Hall of Administration, 500 W. Temple St. 
</P>
<P>
 The MTA's Board of Directors will consider increasing the basic bus fare from 
$1.10 to $1.50, separate peak and off-peak fares, an increase in the cost of 
monthly bus passes and reductions in weekend and holiday service. 
</P>
<P>
 Formal public comment will be taken at the Saturday meeting and letters may be 
sent to the attention of Fare/Service Adjustments, Office of the MTA Secretary, 
Los Angeles County MTA, P.O. Box 194, Los Angeles 90053. 
</P>
